      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until softened</p>",
